WEBVTT

00:02:14.657 --> 00:02:17.368
I prepared the insurance claim documents.

00:02:34.510 --> 00:02:35.636
Good job.

00:02:35.719 --> 00:02:36.553
Yes, sir.

00:02:37.554 --> 00:02:40.015
INSURANCE CLAIM FORM

00:03:12.339 --> 00:03:13.340
Around the world,

00:03:14.299 --> 00:03:16.760
ugly deals happen behind closed doors.

00:03:18.012 --> 00:03:18.846
Just a moment, sir.

00:03:21.473 --> 00:03:22.641
A single medical certificate.

00:03:23.976 --> 00:03:25.269
A one-line accident report.

00:03:27.479 --> 00:03:29.773
As you trace the hidden truth
on that sheet of paper,

00:03:31.066 --> 00:03:32.860
you may come across scumbags

00:03:34.028 --> 00:03:35.654
who trade human lives for money.

00:03:37.071 --> 00:03:38.449
Digging into all of this…

00:03:40.325 --> 00:03:41.493
is my job.

00:03:42.327 --> 00:03:43.162
It's gone cold.

00:03:43.245 --> 00:03:44.371
Add more steam.

00:03:51.295 --> 00:03:53.464
Damn it.

00:03:55.340 --> 00:03:56.341
Hey.

00:03:56.842 --> 00:03:57.676
Who the hell are you?

00:03:57.760 --> 00:03:59.553
Relax.

00:03:59.636 --> 00:04:00.888
I'm not in your line of work.

00:04:01.889 --> 00:04:03.348
You're out of your damn mind.

00:04:04.183 --> 00:04:05.267
Do you know who I am?

00:05:05.536 --> 00:05:07.162
I noticed you were pretty well insured.

00:05:08.330 --> 00:05:09.456
How many should I chop off?

00:06:28.785 --> 00:06:30.495
Kim, a man in his thirties,

00:06:30.579 --> 00:06:33.457
has been arrested for arranging
intentional finger amputations

00:06:33.540 --> 00:06:36.251
to claim workers' compensation payouts
worth billions of won.

00:06:37.044 --> 00:06:39.504
Kim used promises of high profit
to recruit participants,

00:06:39.588 --> 00:06:42.925
persuaded them to amputate their fingers,
and had them sign up for workers' comp,

00:06:43.008 --> 00:06:46.887
ultimately pocketing around
three billion won in fraudulent claims.

00:06:46.970 --> 00:06:47.930
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

00:06:48.013 --> 00:06:51.183
The police have uncovered a scheme
in which job seekers,

00:06:51.266 --> 00:06:52.768
including foreign workers,

00:06:52.851 --> 00:06:56.230
were lured into work
and intentionally harmed on the job

00:06:56.312 --> 00:06:58.815
to collect tens of billions of won
in insurance…

00:07:02.486 --> 00:07:05.405
Thanks to you, Mr. Cha,
we lost another group contract.

00:07:05.489 --> 00:07:06.365
Right.

00:07:06.448 --> 00:07:07.991
But we saved over ten times on the payout.

00:07:11.536 --> 00:07:12.537
Yes.

00:07:14.623 --> 00:07:15.666
Excuse me?

00:07:17.834 --> 00:07:20.003
Oh, I'm terribly sorry.

00:07:20.087 --> 00:07:23.507
It's not just any barber shop,
but a private one.

00:07:23.590 --> 00:07:25.217
Right, and it's members-only.

00:07:25.300 --> 00:07:26.885
Of course, we'll make sure
you're compensated.

00:07:26.969 --> 00:07:28.220
Yes, I'm sorry about that.

00:07:33.600 --> 00:07:34.977
What's the point of saving on the payout

00:07:35.060 --> 00:07:37.020
if all the operating funds
go to cleaning up after you?

00:07:37.687 --> 00:07:39.523
Maybe I'll take a vacation, then.

00:07:39.606 --> 00:07:41.316
With no operating funds,
I might as well rest.

00:07:41.900 --> 00:07:44.695
That's not what I'm saying.
I'm just asking you not to overdo it.

00:07:44.778 --> 00:07:47.489
You could call the police
instead of handling it yourself.

00:07:47.572 --> 00:07:50.325
You know they never arrive on time.

00:07:50.409 --> 00:07:52.286
Mr. Cha! I've got bad news.

00:07:52.828 --> 00:07:54.329
Do you remember Chae-rin?

00:08:01.795 --> 00:08:03.588
This is all my fault.

00:08:04.881 --> 00:08:07.092
I've been struggling to get by
since my divorce

00:08:07.175 --> 00:08:08.593
and had to leave my child alone.

00:08:09.803 --> 00:08:12.764
I know you're worried,
but I heard what happened from her.

00:08:13.265 --> 00:08:15.434
It's a huge relief
that you have insurance.

00:08:16.393 --> 00:08:19.562
My poor Chae-rin.
I don't know what to do now.

00:08:45.130 --> 00:08:46.840
She has third-degree burns
on 40% of her body.

00:08:47.758 --> 00:08:49.301
Her mother already filed
an insurance claim.

00:08:52.929 --> 00:08:54.222
I rubbed my eyes a lot

00:08:54.931 --> 00:08:57.142
while I was asleep…

00:08:58.894 --> 00:09:01.271
and couldn't see the next day.

00:09:01.355 --> 00:09:03.148
1 YEAR AGO

00:09:03.231 --> 00:09:04.316
Really?

00:09:04.399 --> 00:09:05.400
Yes.

00:09:05.484 --> 00:09:08.487
But my mom gave me a lot of pocket money

00:09:08.570 --> 00:09:10.197
because I had a rough time being unwell.

00:09:13.533 --> 00:09:16.828
With this, you can play video games,
buy snacks,

00:09:16.912 --> 00:09:18.705
and even try the claw machine.

00:09:20.874 --> 00:09:21.958
Are you giving this to me?

00:09:22.834 --> 00:09:23.668
Yes.

00:09:25.170 --> 00:09:26.088
Thank you.

00:09:41.436 --> 00:09:43.145
Mr. Cha.

00:09:44.106 --> 00:09:46.650
It really was an accident.

00:09:47.150 --> 00:09:49.444
I was trying to eat instant noodles,

00:09:50.612 --> 00:09:52.531
but I spilled them.

00:09:55.700 --> 00:09:56.743
Chae-rin…

00:10:00.163 --> 00:10:01.832
I'll stop by tomorrow for a test drive.

00:10:01.915 --> 00:10:03.375
Okay, see you tomorrow.

00:10:05.627 --> 00:10:06.878
Big money coming in, I see.

00:10:10.298 --> 00:10:11.633
Fifty million won for loss of vision.

00:10:13.343 --> 00:10:14.678
Seventy million for the burn injuries.

00:10:17.013 --> 00:10:17.848
What's next?

00:10:20.517 --> 00:10:22.561
The police ruled it an accident.
Who are you to say anything?

00:10:22.644 --> 00:10:24.312
You still call yourself a mother?

00:10:25.564 --> 00:10:27.190
That kid is lying
to protect a mother like you…

00:10:29.234 --> 00:10:30.861
even though she almost died.

00:10:33.822 --> 00:10:34.781
I'll make sure…

00:10:36.366 --> 00:10:37.409
to put you behind bars.

00:10:42.539 --> 00:10:44.166
VIP INVITATION SPECIAL AUCTION

00:10:55.010 --> 00:10:56.052
This way.

00:10:59.014 --> 00:11:00.765
I'm looking forward to this.

00:11:04.311 --> 00:11:05.145
What's this?

00:11:05.228 --> 00:11:07.189
Ms. Kim, you must've worked so hard.

00:11:07.272 --> 00:11:08.106
Not at all.

00:11:08.190 --> 00:11:11.401
When did you prepare this?
Just look at the colors.

00:11:11.485 --> 00:11:12.903
Now this is art.

00:11:14.112 --> 00:11:16.198
Well done!

00:11:16.281 --> 00:11:17.365
It's all thanks to you.

00:12:10.919 --> 00:12:11.795
Hey!

00:12:12.546 --> 00:12:14.256
-What the heck?
-Are you insane?

00:12:14.339 --> 00:12:16.091
Do you know how much this is worth?

00:12:16.174 --> 00:12:17.842
What the hell do you think you're doing?!

00:12:21.054 --> 00:12:22.055
That's what I want to ask.

00:12:22.138 --> 00:12:23.306
Ms. Han!

00:12:23.932 --> 00:12:26.685
Tell me what the hell is going on!

00:12:27.519 --> 00:12:30.105
Please get rid of this
before the clients arrive.

00:12:41.866 --> 00:12:43.076
How could you tear up a work of art?

00:12:43.159 --> 00:12:44.828
You're the chief auctioneer.

00:12:45.495 --> 00:12:46.496
Which is it?

00:12:46.580 --> 00:12:49.374
If you knew it was a forgery,
then you committed a crime.

00:12:49.457 --> 00:12:50.625
If you didn't,

00:12:50.709 --> 00:12:52.586
then you don't deserve
to be an auctioneer.

00:12:52.669 --> 00:12:54.087
It's not a forgery.

00:12:54.170 --> 00:12:56.256
It was consigned to me
by Artist Jeong's son.

00:12:56.339 --> 00:12:57.257
Artist Jeong

00:12:57.340 --> 00:12:59.759
suffered a stroke
and is in a nursing facility.

00:12:59.843 --> 00:13:01.219
He can't even hold a brush.

00:13:04.347 --> 00:13:06.099
But the appraiser said…

00:13:06.600 --> 00:13:08.018
Had we sold that painting,

00:13:08.560 --> 00:13:10.270
not only would it have humiliated
the auction house,

00:13:10.353 --> 00:13:12.939
but it would've made you legally liable.

00:13:14.024 --> 00:13:16.693
I'm going to investigate this thoroughly,

00:13:16.776 --> 00:13:17.611
so be prepared.

00:13:48.433 --> 00:13:55.023
THE LATE CHA WOO-HEE
OCTOBER 8, 1993 - AUGUST 28, 2020

00:14:14.125 --> 00:14:16.711
Although the circumstances are suspicious,

00:14:16.795 --> 00:14:20.173
there's no objective evidence
that the accident was intentional.

00:14:21.633 --> 00:14:22.467
You bastard.

00:14:23.593 --> 00:14:24.761
Let go of me!

00:14:24.844 --> 00:14:25.887
Keep still!

00:14:50.495 --> 00:14:53.039
REDEVELOPMENT THAT IGNORES
THE RESIDENTS MUST STOP!

00:15:09.097 --> 00:15:10.181
HYUN-SU'S FRUIT

00:15:13.101 --> 00:15:14.894
I didn't lie like my friends did

00:15:14.978 --> 00:15:16.771
and was honest about
taking a trip with my boyfriend.

00:15:17.731 --> 00:15:18.898
So trust me, okay?

00:15:27.782 --> 00:15:28.783
POLICYHOLDER: CHA WOO-HEE

00:15:28.867 --> 00:15:30.076
BENEFICIARY: JU HYUN-SU

00:15:32.954 --> 00:15:34.038
As only the charge of causing

00:15:34.122 --> 00:15:36.082
the victim's death through negligence
has been sustained,

00:15:36.166 --> 00:15:37.917
the defendant, Ju Hyun-su,

00:15:38.001 --> 00:15:39.669
is hereby sentenced to one year in prison.

00:15:42.630 --> 00:15:43.923
I'll never be fooled again.

00:15:46.468 --> 00:15:47.385
Never.

00:15:50.180 --> 00:15:54.058
MAY YOU ALWAYS ACHIEVE GREATER SUCCESS

00:15:54.726 --> 00:15:57.854
VIP INVITATION SPECIAL AUCTION

00:16:52.992 --> 00:16:55.370
Ms. Han is here.

00:17:22.396 --> 00:17:23.522
VIP INVITATION SPECIAL AUCTION

00:17:25.149 --> 00:17:26.401
We'll begin now.

00:17:56.556 --> 00:18:00.810
This is Black Ink & Light
by Ahn Byeong-woon.

00:18:00.894 --> 00:18:02.103
We'll open at 100 million won

00:18:02.186 --> 00:18:04.898
and take bids
in ten million won increments.

00:18:04.981 --> 00:18:06.274
100 million?

00:18:06.357 --> 00:18:07.191
110 million?

00:18:07.734 --> 00:18:08.735
120 million?

00:18:09.319 --> 00:18:10.320
130 million?

00:18:11.070 --> 00:18:14.532
Next up, we have Genuine Comfort
by Hanna Lien.

00:18:14.616 --> 00:18:16.242
This is a symbolic piece

00:18:16.326 --> 00:18:20.538
that embodies pets as a metaphor
to reflect the essence of human society.

00:18:20.622 --> 00:18:24.375
I look forward to seeing
who the successful bidder will be.

00:18:24.834 --> 00:18:27.712
160 million won? At 160 million.

00:18:28.504 --> 00:18:30.214
170 million won?

00:18:32.926 --> 00:18:35.303
Now, for the moment
we've been waiting for.

00:18:35.386 --> 00:18:36.930
The highlight of today's auction,

00:18:37.513 --> 00:18:39.891
Universe by Choi Jung-soo.

00:18:39.974 --> 00:18:42.477
This is a monumental work by Choi Jung-soo

00:18:42.560 --> 00:18:45.521
that pushes the boundaries
of contemporary painting.

00:18:45.605 --> 00:18:47.982
This piece combines painting, textiles,

00:18:48.066 --> 00:18:50.652
and the physical properties of light,

00:18:50.735 --> 00:18:52.737
making it one of their signature works.

00:18:52.820 --> 00:18:57.450
This lot is expected to achieve
the highest bid of today's auction.

00:18:57.533 --> 00:18:59.786
Let's open the bidding.

00:19:02.080 --> 00:19:03.289
4.85 billion won?

00:19:04.457 --> 00:19:06.209
We have 4.85 billion.

00:19:06.292 --> 00:19:07.710
4.9 billion won?

00:19:07.794 --> 00:19:09.837
We have a 4.9 billion absentee bid.

00:19:11.089 --> 00:19:12.382
4.95 billion won?

00:19:13.007 --> 00:19:15.259
We have 4.95 billion won.

00:19:15.343 --> 00:19:16.469
Five billion won?

00:19:18.137 --> 00:19:19.847
We have a five billion won absentee bid.

00:19:19.931 --> 00:19:21.683
5.05 billion?

00:19:22.642 --> 00:19:23.893
5.05 billion?

00:19:23.977 --> 00:19:25.103
We have 5.05 billion won.

00:19:25.186 --> 00:19:28.064
The highest bid so far
is 5.05 billion won.

00:19:28.147 --> 00:19:28.982
5.1 billion?

00:19:29.065 --> 00:19:31.442
I'm checking the floor.
We have 5.1 billion.

00:19:31.526 --> 00:19:33.528
We received a bid for 5.1 billion.

00:19:34.821 --> 00:19:35.697
5.15 billion?

00:19:37.323 --> 00:19:39.158
We have 5.15 billion.

00:19:40.326 --> 00:19:42.870
5.2 billion won?

00:19:46.541 --> 00:19:48.793
We have 5.2 billion.

00:19:48.876 --> 00:19:52.505
Paddle 86 currently holds
the highest bid at 5.2 billion won.

00:19:52.588 --> 00:19:55.049
Anyone at 5.25 billion?

00:19:56.050 --> 00:19:58.469
We have 5.25 billion for Paddle 64.

00:19:58.970 --> 00:20:01.556
Looking for 5.3 billion.

00:20:02.140 --> 00:20:03.558
Yes, Paddle 86.

00:20:04.183 --> 00:20:05.351
We have 5.3 billion.

00:20:05.435 --> 00:20:07.020
That's the highest bid.

00:20:07.770 --> 00:20:11.441
Let me ask bidders in the room
and on the phone again.

00:20:11.524 --> 00:20:13.067
5.35 billion?

00:20:14.277 --> 00:20:17.655
It may take a little while to decide,

00:20:18.322 --> 00:20:19.991
so I'll give you some time to consider.

00:20:20.074 --> 00:20:22.076
We're bidding at 5.35 billion won.

00:20:22.160 --> 00:20:24.746
I'll call it three times
before closing the bidding.

00:20:27.040 --> 00:20:28.875
5.35 billion?

00:20:31.919 --> 00:20:33.671
5.35 billion?

00:20:34.922 --> 00:20:36.466
5.35 billion?

00:20:40.094 --> 00:20:41.345
After an intense bidding,

00:20:41.429 --> 00:20:44.974
Paddle 86 has secured the lot
at 5.3 billion won.

00:21:22.595 --> 00:21:23.888
Come on.

00:21:27.016 --> 00:21:28.184
I give up.

00:21:28.267 --> 00:21:30.436
What if Mr. Song sees you?

00:21:40.696 --> 00:21:42.240
Why are you still here?

00:21:42.782 --> 00:21:43.783
For market research.

00:21:44.367 --> 00:21:47.203
I want to see which type of champagne
the guests prefer.

00:21:47.829 --> 00:21:49.997
Seriously? You didn't say a word earlier.

00:21:50.081 --> 00:21:53.000
You're already dealing with a lot,
so I didn't want to bother you.

00:21:53.918 --> 00:21:55.461
I'll leave after a bit.

00:21:55.545 --> 00:21:56.379
By the way,

00:21:57.839 --> 00:22:00.508
she's the associate auctioneer, right?

00:22:01.634 --> 00:22:02.468
Why do you ask?

00:22:04.220 --> 00:22:05.096
No reason.

00:22:05.596 --> 00:22:07.306
I just get a bad vibe from her.

00:22:09.016 --> 00:22:09.851
I'll be back.

00:22:29.954 --> 00:22:30.913
Are you okay?

00:22:34.417 --> 00:22:36.043
Yes, I'm fine.

00:22:36.127 --> 00:22:40.006
Thank you for helping me
secure such a great piece today.

00:22:40.089 --> 00:22:42.300
I've only placed bids online before,

00:22:43.426 --> 00:22:45.303
but live auctions are much more fun.

00:22:45.928 --> 00:22:48.764
I noticed you eyeing that piece
at the auction preview,

00:22:48.848 --> 00:22:50.391
so I knew you'd be here today.

00:22:53.060 --> 00:22:54.478
You remember me?

00:22:58.316 --> 00:22:59.859
I don't believe we've actually met before.

00:23:01.944 --> 00:23:05.114
Once I see someone, I don't forget them.

00:23:07.992 --> 00:23:09.076
You don't forget, huh?

00:23:18.419 --> 00:23:19.420
Ever?

00:23:34.060 --> 00:23:35.269
I'm Paek Jun-beom.

00:23:39.482 --> 00:23:40.608
I'm Han Seol-ah.

00:23:41.234 --> 00:23:42.526
It's a pleasure to meet you.

00:23:51.118 --> 00:23:53.454
You're Mr. Paek Jun-beom,
CEO of Your Home, right?

00:23:59.043 --> 00:24:01.837
The artwork you selected today
was exceptional.

00:24:01.921 --> 00:24:04.799
I hear you've got all
the most sought-after pieces these days.

00:24:05.800 --> 00:24:07.760
This is our associate auctioneer.

00:24:07.843 --> 00:24:09.470
She's very good at what she does,

00:24:09.553 --> 00:24:10.805
so I'll leave you two to talk.

00:24:10.888 --> 00:24:11.722
Please excuse me.

00:24:13.766 --> 00:24:14.767
Wait…

00:24:15.351 --> 00:24:16.644
I'm Kim Yun-ji.

00:24:17.353 --> 00:24:20.439
If you have any pieces to consign
for the next auction,

00:24:20.523 --> 00:24:21.774
please allow me to handle them.

00:24:30.950 --> 00:24:33.452
"Associate Auctioneer Kim Yun-ji"?

00:24:35.705 --> 00:24:36.539
Yes, sir.

00:24:41.419 --> 00:24:43.004
You don't know when to step in

00:24:44.630 --> 00:24:46.132
and when to stay back, do you?

00:25:13.409 --> 00:25:14.243
TRANQUILIZER

00:25:24.712 --> 00:25:27.673
Ms. Kim, we're still on the job.

00:25:28.174 --> 00:25:29.008
So?

00:25:30.301 --> 00:25:31.469
I smell alcohol on you.

00:25:32.094 --> 00:25:33.971
You should be careful
when you deal with VIPs.

00:25:35.056 --> 00:25:37.391
Are you sure you're not just upset
that I butted in earlier?

00:25:48.527 --> 00:25:49.820
Ms. Kim Yun-ji.

00:25:51.989 --> 00:25:54.241
Let's behave like professionals.

00:25:57.078 --> 00:25:57.995
You know,

00:25:58.746 --> 00:26:00.122
you've got quite the mental strength.

00:26:02.875 --> 00:26:04.835
You're definitely a professional, Ms. Han.

00:26:08.005 --> 00:26:10.132
Isn't wanting to die
the normal response at this point?

00:26:15.096 --> 00:26:16.514
What are you trying to say?

00:26:20.768 --> 00:26:21.727
I'm curious.

00:26:22.436 --> 00:26:25.481
If the secret you've been hiding
is out in the open,

00:26:26.440 --> 00:26:27.983
would you still be so composed?

00:26:30.236 --> 00:26:32.154
I'm curious to see the look on your face

00:26:32.738 --> 00:26:34.323
when I take the main podium from you.

00:26:39.036 --> 00:26:40.121
The main podium?

00:26:41.747 --> 00:26:42.790
With your skills?

00:26:49.255 --> 00:26:50.714
I won't hold back anymore.

00:26:52.842 --> 00:26:54.260
Enjoy what time you have left.

00:26:54.343 --> 00:26:56.178
Not that there's much of it.

00:27:26.792 --> 00:27:27.626
Hello?

00:27:29.545 --> 00:27:30.463
Mr. Cha Woo-seok?

00:27:31.964 --> 00:27:32.923
Yes. Who's this?

00:27:35.134 --> 00:27:37.136
I want to report insurance fraud.

00:27:38.846 --> 00:27:39.722
Insurance fraud?

00:27:41.265 --> 00:27:42.850
Sure, go ahead.

00:27:45.019 --> 00:27:45.853
It's a murder.

00:27:47.521 --> 00:27:49.523
A murder committed
for an insurance payout.

00:27:52.485 --> 00:27:54.487
Why did you call me instead of the police?

00:27:56.530 --> 00:27:59.533
The police can't be trusted.
They dismissed this case as an accident.

00:28:01.577 --> 00:28:03.412
I've heard rumors about you.

00:28:04.079 --> 00:28:06.582
Once you're after something,
you never let it go.

00:28:11.879 --> 00:28:14.131
You're the only person I can trust now.

00:28:14.924 --> 00:28:16.509
I'll tell you everything I know.

00:28:25.726 --> 00:28:26.852
When did you get here?

00:28:28.229 --> 00:28:29.897
Just let me sleep.

00:28:29.980 --> 00:28:31.482
I've been on a stakeout
for three days in a row.

00:28:32.358 --> 00:28:34.568
Go home and sleep comfortably, then.

00:28:34.652 --> 00:28:36.111
It's too far.

00:28:38.113 --> 00:28:39.865
Where are you going at this hour?

00:28:40.449 --> 00:28:41.867
I got a tip
about a murder-for-insurance case.

00:28:43.994 --> 00:28:45.538
Go back to being a cop already.

00:28:49.375 --> 00:28:50.292
It's in your jurisdiction.

00:29:12.773 --> 00:29:13.899
Your call cannot be connected.

00:29:13.983 --> 00:29:17.528
You will be directed to voicemail,
and charges will apply after the…

00:29:22.366 --> 00:29:23.742
She's not answering.

00:29:36.797 --> 00:29:37.715
What the heck?

00:29:49.226 --> 00:29:52.771
SIU INVESTIGATOR CHA WOO-SEOK

00:30:04.867 --> 00:30:05.909
MISSED CALL

00:30:13.167 --> 00:30:15.169
Please don't take any photos!

00:30:15.252 --> 00:30:16.754
Move out of the way!

00:30:47.826 --> 00:30:48.827
Three meters?

00:30:49.328 --> 00:30:52.748
Yes, they said she landed
three meters away from the exterior wall.

00:30:53.582 --> 00:30:55.125
The distance doesn't quite add up.

00:30:55.751 --> 00:30:56.669
No, it doesn't.

00:30:56.752 --> 00:30:58.128
If she'd slipped or committed suicide,

00:30:58.212 --> 00:30:59.963
she would've landed within two meters.

00:31:01.131 --> 00:31:03.050
Secure the CCTV footage
from the auction house,

00:31:03.133 --> 00:31:04.968
and trace her whereabouts
around the time of the fall.

00:31:05.928 --> 00:31:06.762
Got it.

00:31:13.185 --> 00:31:17.022
Her legs, lower back, ribs, and spine
have all been fractured.

00:31:17.106 --> 00:31:19.733
The fracture pattern is typical of a fall.

00:31:19.817 --> 00:31:23.529
The direct cause of death is organ failure
due to multiple fractures.

00:31:25.072 --> 00:31:26.657
Is this a suicide, then?

00:31:27.866 --> 00:31:30.953
That's the most plausible hypothesis,

00:31:31.036 --> 00:31:34.707
but I found minute petechiae
around her neck and inside her lips.

00:31:36.500 --> 00:31:38.711
Are you saying she was strangled?

00:31:38.794 --> 00:31:39.753
No.

00:31:39.837 --> 00:31:42.631
The petechiae are too faint
to make that conclusion.

00:31:42.715 --> 00:31:46.176
But it's possible
someone suddenly grabbed her by the neck.

00:31:54.101 --> 00:31:56.311
GANGHA POLICE STATION

00:31:56.395 --> 00:31:57.438
This can't be a coincidence.

00:31:58.147 --> 00:31:59.189
What happened?

00:32:00.482 --> 00:32:03.819
The victim was going to report
an insurance-related murder.

00:32:03.902 --> 00:32:06.739
So you went to see her,
and she just fell to her death?

00:32:07.364 --> 00:32:08.532
Yes, sir.

00:32:08.615 --> 00:32:10.367
And Cha Woo-seok received the tip?

00:32:16.081 --> 00:32:18.792
Hey, Ggong.
You and I will handle this case.

00:32:18.876 --> 00:32:19.710
Excuse me?

00:32:20.586 --> 00:32:22.546
Sir, Eun-gyeom and I can…

00:32:22.629 --> 00:32:25.799
I won't have Cha Woo-seok
poking around in our jurisdiction.

00:32:25.883 --> 00:32:28.302
But you're okay with running into him?

00:32:28.385 --> 00:32:29.636
He won't be okay with it,

00:32:30.679 --> 00:32:33.056
since he still thinks
I let his sister's killer walk free.

00:32:39.563 --> 00:32:40.731
Is that what you think too?

00:32:42.065 --> 00:32:44.985
I think we all did what we could
from our own point of view.

00:32:45.068 --> 00:32:46.904
A case has no point of view.
There's only the truth.

00:32:46.987 --> 00:32:49.156
And if you can't accept that,
you'll end up like Cha Woo-seok.

00:33:06.381 --> 00:33:07.966
We'll investigate again
since you filed a report,

00:33:08.634 --> 00:33:09.843
but if she continues to deny it,

00:33:11.011 --> 00:33:12.387
there's nothing else we can do.

00:33:13.514 --> 00:33:14.348
Goodbye, then.

00:33:19.186 --> 00:33:20.020
What should we do?

00:33:20.979 --> 00:33:22.022
We'll come every day

00:33:23.023 --> 00:33:25.275
to show her there are other adults
who will protect her.

00:33:33.325 --> 00:33:34.243
You head back first.

00:33:34.326 --> 00:33:35.911
I'm going to stop by Royal Auction.

00:33:35.994 --> 00:33:37.079
Okay.

00:33:37.162 --> 00:33:39.706
Oh, Ms. Kim Yun-ji's case
was ruled a suicide, right?

00:33:39.790 --> 00:33:41.750
This month marks two years
since she took out the policy,

00:33:41.834 --> 00:33:43.502
and the suicide exclusion period
has passed too.

00:33:43.585 --> 00:33:46.046
She wanted to report a murder
committed for an insurance payout.

00:33:46.755 --> 00:33:47.714
An hour before she died.

00:33:49.550 --> 00:33:51.051
Would someone
on the verge of suicide do that?

00:34:56.491 --> 00:34:57.951
-Let me give you a hand.
-Oh, thank you.

00:39:01.444 --> 00:39:03.155
Damn it.

00:39:14.583 --> 00:39:15.917
That's it!

00:39:16.501 --> 00:39:18.211
The blades turned away.

00:39:18.837 --> 00:39:21.089
Funny how it worked when you showed up.

00:39:22.090 --> 00:39:24.259
I guess Ms. Kim didn't like you.

00:39:27.220 --> 00:39:29.055
Our company is a mess right now.

00:39:32.184 --> 00:39:33.101
My apologies.

00:39:35.729 --> 00:39:36.605
Chair Kim.

00:39:40.233 --> 00:39:42.152
The police are coming to investigate.

00:39:43.195 --> 00:39:46.239
This final year of misfortune
is making quite a commotion.

00:39:47.657 --> 00:39:48.783
I'm sorry, ma'am.

00:39:49.826 --> 00:39:52.662
I should've been more attentive
to my team member.

00:39:53.413 --> 00:39:55.582
I'll take care of the police.

00:39:55.665 --> 00:39:58.293
Well, you're in charge of PR as well,
so you should.

00:40:01.338 --> 00:40:03.089
Then what's the point
of having a managing director?

00:40:04.132 --> 00:40:07.302
Right, it makes more sense that I meet
with them on behalf of the company.

00:40:07.844 --> 00:40:11.056
They'll want to speak with someone
who worked closely with Ms. Kim.

00:40:11.640 --> 00:40:12.891
If Mr. Song talks to them,

00:40:13.475 --> 00:40:15.894
it could make the situation
seem more serious.

00:40:16.519 --> 00:40:17.729
You sure you'll be okay?

00:40:18.730 --> 00:40:19.898
Yes.

00:40:19.981 --> 00:40:23.235
I'll make sure this is dealt with quietly.

00:40:24.110 --> 00:40:24.945
All right.

00:40:27.197 --> 00:40:28.531
Quietly…

00:40:29.366 --> 00:40:30.700
I like the sound of that.

00:40:40.377 --> 00:40:41.253
Hello.

00:40:41.336 --> 00:40:45.048
I'm Chief Auctioneer Han Seol-ah
at Royal Auction.

00:40:45.131 --> 00:40:46.508
I'm Detective Pyo Seong-il
from Gangha Police Station.

00:40:46.591 --> 00:40:48.301
I'm Gong Joo-young.

00:40:49.219 --> 00:40:51.846
This is just a basic inquiry
into the incident,

00:40:51.930 --> 00:40:53.431
so there's no need to feel any pressure.

00:40:53.515 --> 00:40:55.475
Okay, please take a seat.

00:40:55.558 --> 00:40:56.559
Okay.

00:40:58.937 --> 00:40:59.813
First off,

00:41:00.313 --> 00:41:02.732
can you tell me about that night?

00:41:04.192 --> 00:41:08.655
There was an event exclusive
to Royal Auction VIP members,

00:41:08.738 --> 00:41:11.408
followed by an after-party
that went on until around 10 p.m.

00:41:11.992 --> 00:41:14.202
What role did Ms. Kim Yun-ji have?

00:41:15.620 --> 00:41:17.080
She was an associate auctioneer.

00:41:22.002 --> 00:41:24.587
No CCTV cameras
in the emergency staircase.

00:42:02.834 --> 00:42:04.836
A murder committed
for an insurance payout.

00:42:06.296 --> 00:42:08.006
I'll tell you everything I know.

00:42:10.342 --> 00:42:11.760
After that, she committed suicide here?

00:42:12.302 --> 00:42:15.263
Did you notice anything unusual
about Ms. Kim that day?

00:42:15.347 --> 00:42:16.848
Did she perhaps get into an argument
with someone?

00:42:17.474 --> 00:42:20.310
She seemed fine from what I could tell.

00:42:20.393 --> 00:42:22.604
As her colleague, do you have any idea
what might've happened?

00:42:22.687 --> 00:42:24.564
I didn't know much about her private life.

00:42:24.647 --> 00:42:25.857
CHIEF AUCTIONEER: HAN SEOL-AH

00:42:26.524 --> 00:42:28.693
How many auctioneers
does the company have?

00:42:29.778 --> 00:42:31.613
Ms. Kim and I are the only ones
who actually run the auctions.

00:42:31.696 --> 00:42:33.615
Everyone else is still in training.

00:42:34.449 --> 00:42:37.452
Can we get the list of event participants?

00:42:37.994 --> 00:42:40.205
The VIP list is confidential,

00:42:40.288 --> 00:42:41.956
so it can't be released.

00:42:42.749 --> 00:42:44.751
They're witnesses who were at the scene.

00:42:44.834 --> 00:42:46.378
One of them could be a suspect.

00:42:51.674 --> 00:42:54.511
Is there any evidence
that it was a murder?

00:42:56.054 --> 00:42:57.305
Your colleague is dead,

00:42:57.389 --> 00:42:59.641
but protecting your clients
is more important to you?

00:43:00.141 --> 00:43:00.975
Detective Gong.

00:43:02.977 --> 00:43:04.229
Please bring a warrant.

00:43:04.813 --> 00:43:06.064
If you have more questions,

00:43:06.147 --> 00:43:08.274
please send them in writing.

00:43:09.651 --> 00:43:12.529
When was the last time
you saw Ms. Kim Yun-ji that day?

00:43:13.905 --> 00:43:16.324
Where were you
at the time of the incident?

00:43:21.037 --> 00:43:22.330
Was that a difficult question?

00:43:23.289 --> 00:43:24.374
It seems like you can't answer.

00:43:25.792 --> 00:43:27.961
I was in the Auction Team office.

00:43:28.545 --> 00:43:31.464
I didn't see her again
after the after-party.

00:43:33.842 --> 00:43:37.053
This is the extent of the cooperation
I can provide.

00:44:08.626 --> 00:44:11.129
If it seems too perfect,
there's a good chance it's not true.

00:44:11.963 --> 00:44:13.006
I'll look into Han Seol-ah

00:44:13.089 --> 00:44:15.300
and her relationship with Kim Yun-ji.

00:44:17.427 --> 00:44:18.636
So there is something, huh?

00:44:22.849 --> 00:44:24.517
I don't expect much from the police,

00:44:25.143 --> 00:44:26.144
but let's help each other out.

00:44:26.227 --> 00:44:27.437
No thanks.

00:44:27.520 --> 00:44:29.355
Forget the easy way
and go the long way, then.

00:44:29.439 --> 00:44:30.648
Just go sell insurance.

00:44:30.732 --> 00:44:32.734
You still think you're a detective?

00:44:34.360 --> 00:44:35.778
I get that a lot from my boss.

00:44:38.031 --> 00:44:39.032
Let's go.

00:44:40.408 --> 00:44:42.911
It's funny how cops
are good at taking small bribes,

00:44:42.994 --> 00:44:44.787
but they can't sniff out big money.

00:44:46.623 --> 00:44:47.749
Watch yourself.

00:44:48.875 --> 00:44:50.126
Why are you angry?

00:44:51.419 --> 00:44:52.420
Do you have regrets?

00:44:53.505 --> 00:44:54.380
Do I make you uncomfortable?

00:44:54.964 --> 00:44:56.174
You little bastard.

00:44:56.758 --> 00:44:58.968
What are you two doing?
You can't do this here!

00:45:02.764 --> 00:45:03.640
Hey, Ggong.

00:45:03.723 --> 00:45:05.099
If even one investigation detail

00:45:06.017 --> 00:45:08.061
gets leaked to the insurance company,

00:45:08.144 --> 00:45:09.229
be prepared to lose your job.

00:45:18.530 --> 00:45:22.033
TYPE: PERFECT ONLIFE SWITCH INSURANCE
POLICYHOLDER: KIM YUN-JI

00:45:22.617 --> 00:45:25.495
Kim Yun-ji was treated for depression
for a long time.

00:45:25.578 --> 00:45:27.997
I'm seeing a lot of signs
that point to suicide.

00:45:29.123 --> 00:45:30.416
What did the people
at the auction house say?

00:45:30.500 --> 00:45:33.419
The chief auctioneer showed up,
but she wasn't cooperative.

00:45:33.503 --> 00:45:34.337
Han Seol-ah, was it?

00:45:35.255 --> 00:45:36.130
It's this woman.

00:45:41.886 --> 00:45:44.138
ART AUCTION HOUSE "ROYAL AUCTION"
REVENUE UP 28% FROM LAST YEAR

00:45:58.903 --> 00:45:59.862
Han Seol-ah.

00:46:11.791 --> 00:46:13.668
HAN SEOL-AH

00:46:15.128 --> 00:46:17.797
FIRST FEMALE CHIEF AUCTIONEER
AT ROYAL AUCTION

00:46:19.507 --> 00:46:21.634
THE CINDERELLA OF THE AUCTION WORLD
CHIEF AUCTIONEER HAN SEOL-AH

00:46:24.804 --> 00:46:27.223
"I DON'T LOOK, I READ THE ROOM"

00:46:29.183 --> 00:46:30.393
"PEOPLE THINK AUCTIONEERS JUST CALL BIDS…"

00:46:30.476 --> 00:46:31.769
HAN SEOL-AH ENTERED THE AUCTION WORLD
8 YEARS AGO…

00:46:31.853 --> 00:46:33.021
"WINNING A BID
COMES DOWN TO TRUST AND TIMING"

00:46:35.857 --> 00:46:37.609
AUCTIONEER

00:47:42.382 --> 00:47:44.050
Please stop crying.

00:47:44.592 --> 00:47:46.636
Yun-ji…

00:47:46.719 --> 00:47:49.472
I feel so sorry for her.

00:47:50.473 --> 00:47:53.851
She was excited about debuting soon.

00:47:54.936 --> 00:47:55.770
Debut?

00:47:57.230 --> 00:48:01.317
Mr. Song promised to get rid of Ms. Han

00:48:01.401 --> 00:48:05.071
and promote Yun-ji in her place.

00:48:05.154 --> 00:48:06.114
Really?

00:48:07.323 --> 00:48:08.157
Why?

00:48:08.241 --> 00:48:09.992
That's not what's important right now!

00:48:10.076 --> 00:48:12.370
Look at what happened to Yun-ji!

00:48:16.207 --> 00:48:17.208
It's Ms. Han.

00:48:32.682 --> 00:48:34.016
It's probably a battery problem.

00:48:34.976 --> 00:48:36.144
Your smart key, I mean.

00:48:39.021 --> 00:48:40.064
I guess you're right.

00:48:42.108 --> 00:48:43.359
Don't call a tow truck.

00:48:43.818 --> 00:48:45.236
I'll help you.

00:48:45.319 --> 00:48:46.195
Your key fob, please.

00:49:16.142 --> 00:49:18.394
Hold the key fob against the start button
and press it.

00:49:18.936 --> 00:49:20.146
It should start your car.

00:49:24.400 --> 00:49:26.861
Thank you. I owe you one.

00:49:27.528 --> 00:49:28.696
You can pay me back.

00:49:32.450 --> 00:49:34.035
If we ever meet again, that is.

00:50:04.982 --> 00:50:07.068
SOCHEON FUNERAL SERVICE

00:50:34.095 --> 00:50:36.931
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

00:50:54.156 --> 00:50:55.324
VIEW INSURANCE POLICY

00:50:55.408 --> 00:50:56.242
KIM YUN-JI

00:50:56.325 --> 00:50:57.910
TYPE: PERFECT ONLIFE SWITCH INSURANCE

00:50:59.954 --> 00:51:01.956
PARTIES TO THE POLICY
POLICYHOLDER: KIM YUN-JI

00:51:03.749 --> 00:51:05.668
AUTO PAYMENT ACCOUNT DETAILS
NAME: JANGWON BANK

00:51:20.391 --> 00:51:21.976
HAN SEOL-AH

00:51:25.563 --> 00:51:26.564
What?

00:51:29.734 --> 00:51:32.028
POLICYHOLDER: YOON SEUNG-JAE

00:51:32.111 --> 00:51:33.446
Yoon Seung-jae.

00:51:34.196 --> 00:51:35.740
Thirty-five years old.

00:51:36.324 --> 00:51:38.451
The total death benefit
is 700 million won.

00:51:39.785 --> 00:51:41.245
The beneficiary is…

00:51:42.496 --> 00:51:44.040
BENEFICIARY: HAN SEOL-AH

00:51:45.124 --> 00:51:46.334
Han Seol-ah?

00:51:53.591 --> 00:51:55.593
POLICY CHANGE HISTORY

00:51:57.136 --> 00:51:58.054
Canceled?

00:52:03.726 --> 00:52:05.645
YOON SEUNG-JAE
PHONE NUMBER: 010-0532-9655

00:52:10.274 --> 00:52:12.193
The phone you are trying to reach
is turned off.

00:52:12.276 --> 00:52:16.280
You will be directed to voicemail
after the beep and charges…

00:52:27.750 --> 00:52:28.584
Hello?

00:52:30.586 --> 00:52:32.254
Is this Mr. Yoon Seung-jae's home?

00:52:33.005 --> 00:52:35.049
Yes. Who's this?

00:52:35.758 --> 00:52:38.678
Hello, I'm Cha Woo-seok,
an SIU investigator.

00:52:38.761 --> 00:52:41.430
I need to confirm
a few insurance-related matters.

00:52:41.514 --> 00:52:43.099
May I speak to Mr. Yoon Seung-jae?

00:52:46.018 --> 00:52:46.936
Seung-jae…

00:52:48.562 --> 00:52:49.689
is dead.

00:52:50.815 --> 00:52:51.732
He died ten days ago.

00:52:58.072 --> 00:53:00.199
CHANGE DETAILS: CANCELLATION (WITHDRAWAL)
DATE: MAY 23, 2025

00:53:26.392 --> 00:53:28.769
The bride needs to smile more.

00:53:30.146 --> 00:53:31.022
Are you nervous?

00:53:32.106 --> 00:53:33.024
You look so stiff.

00:53:39.113 --> 00:53:40.031
Give me a big smile.

00:53:44.035 --> 00:53:45.119
Now face each other.

00:54:06.182 --> 00:54:07.016
Nice.

00:54:09.226 --> 00:54:10.061
That's nice.

00:54:12.354 --> 00:54:13.981
See? It's much better
now that you're smiling.

00:55:09.370 --> 00:55:10.412
POLICYHOLDER: YOON SEUNG-JAE

00:55:10.496 --> 00:55:12.706
He paid the 200 million premium upfront.

00:55:13.290 --> 00:55:17.711
It's a VIP-only insurance policy
for high-net-worth individuals.

00:55:17.795 --> 00:55:20.047
I think this is the case
Kim Yun-ji was going to report.

00:55:21.423 --> 00:55:22.716
I'm going to the police station.

00:55:25.719 --> 00:55:27.346
Hey, hold on.

00:55:27.429 --> 00:55:28.305
GUARANTEE INSURANCE
WITHDRAWAL/CANCELLATION CONFIRMATION

00:55:28.389 --> 00:55:29.515
What's this?

00:55:30.099 --> 00:55:31.016
It's a cancellation.

00:55:32.393 --> 00:55:33.894
Oh, you're right.

00:55:33.978 --> 00:55:35.729
This won't even count toward performance,
so why…

00:55:36.522 --> 00:55:38.107
Where did he go?

00:55:38.899 --> 00:55:40.484
Is he in detective mode again?

00:55:40.568 --> 00:55:42.987
I never should've brought him here, right?

00:55:43.070 --> 00:55:44.071
It's all my fault, right?

00:55:48.534 --> 00:55:50.870
Her fiancé died just ten days ago.

00:55:51.579 --> 00:55:52.788
Did she file an insurance claim?

00:55:54.081 --> 00:55:55.541
No, that's the strange part.

00:55:56.417 --> 00:55:57.585
The policy was canceled

00:55:58.294 --> 00:55:59.211
right before he died.

00:56:00.212 --> 00:56:01.172
Why did he do that?

00:56:02.089 --> 00:56:05.050
Kim Yun-ji definitely knew something.

00:56:05.134 --> 00:56:06.468
Han Seol-ah

00:56:06.552 --> 00:56:09.013
was about to lose
her chief auctioneer title to Kim Yun-ji.

00:56:09.096 --> 00:56:11.098
From where Han Seol-ah stands,

00:56:11.182 --> 00:56:14.226
Kim Yun-ji's death ended all her troubles.

00:56:16.812 --> 00:56:18.772
Look into the details
of her fiancé's death.

00:56:19.732 --> 00:56:20.733
Okay.

00:56:37.082 --> 00:56:38.209
Han Seol-ah's fiancé

00:56:38.876 --> 00:56:40.044
was in a yacht accident.

00:56:40.753 --> 00:56:42.421
AUTOPSY RESULTS RULE THE DEATH AS DROWNING

00:56:44.924 --> 00:56:45.799
Drowning?

00:57:01.982 --> 00:57:02.858
We meet again.

00:57:04.944 --> 00:57:06.070
Let me officially introduce myself.

00:57:08.155 --> 00:57:10.699
I'm Cha Woo-seok, an SIU investigator.

00:57:12.910 --> 00:57:15.120
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE
SIU SENIOR MANAGER CHA WOO-SEOK

00:57:15.204 --> 00:57:17.623
Ms. Kim Yun-ji was a client of ours.

00:57:17.706 --> 00:57:19.041
That's why I'm investigating

00:57:19.625 --> 00:57:22.086
whether her death was a suicide

00:57:22.962 --> 00:57:24.171
or…

00:57:24.755 --> 00:57:25.756
a murder.

00:57:28.759 --> 00:57:30.636
You sound like a detective.

00:57:31.470 --> 00:57:34.223
Do SIU investigators
handle actual investigations too?

00:57:34.306 --> 00:57:35.557
We at least look into it.

00:57:35.641 --> 00:57:38.185
I told the police everything I know.

00:57:38.769 --> 00:57:41.605
You didn't mention she was competing
for the chief auctioneer position.

00:57:42.398 --> 00:57:44.566
I never considered her as my competition.

00:57:47.152 --> 00:57:48.237
How do you feel?

00:57:51.240 --> 00:57:53.826
Tens of billions of won
are in your hands to decide.

00:57:54.410 --> 00:57:56.412
Raising a couple of hundred million won
would be a piece of cake.

00:57:57.621 --> 00:58:00.165
I bet money doesn't even feel real to you.

00:58:01.000 --> 00:58:02.710
I wonder what your salary is.

00:58:03.502 --> 00:58:05.838
I get the feeling that a regular salary
wouldn't satisfy you.

00:58:08.590 --> 00:58:11.510
An auctioneer is no different
from a regular office worker.

00:58:14.388 --> 00:58:15.389
It must be hard

00:58:16.390 --> 00:58:17.725
for a regular office worker like you

00:58:17.808 --> 00:58:19.643
to be constantly compared
to wealthy clients

00:58:19.727 --> 00:58:22.146
and to need nice clothes
and a nice car for the job.

00:58:24.189 --> 00:58:26.066
That's what most people think,

00:58:26.150 --> 00:58:27.443
only judging by what they see.

00:58:34.533 --> 00:58:36.577
If you're done talking, please excuse me.

00:58:44.752 --> 00:58:45.961
Yoon Seung-jae.

00:58:58.932 --> 00:59:00.851
This is Gong Joo-young
from Violent Crimes Unit 1.

00:59:03.854 --> 00:59:06.148
Hello? I'm listening.

00:59:13.322 --> 00:59:16.575
The woman who died at Royal Auction
didn't commit suicide.

00:59:17.618 --> 00:59:18.702
She was murdered.

00:59:18.786 --> 00:59:20.079
RECORDING

00:59:21.413 --> 00:59:22.748
Are you a witness?

00:59:24.541 --> 00:59:25.376
Hello?

00:59:30.506 --> 00:59:31.423
Yoon Seung-jae.

00:59:32.091 --> 00:59:34.343
A successful businessman
who ran a restaurant.

00:59:34.843 --> 00:59:35.761
Ten days ago,

00:59:36.512 --> 00:59:38.347
he took a yacht out on the river and died.

00:59:38.430 --> 00:59:40.724
The death benefit
amounted to 700 million won,

00:59:41.475 --> 00:59:42.976
and you were the beneficiary.

00:59:44.103 --> 00:59:45.104
You two

00:59:45.729 --> 00:59:46.730
weren't family.

00:59:49.900 --> 00:59:51.318
He was my fiancé.

00:59:52.569 --> 00:59:53.654
Did you already know?

00:59:54.696 --> 00:59:57.366
That he canceled his policy
before he died?

00:59:59.451 --> 01:00:00.536
Yes.

01:00:04.706 --> 01:00:05.707
What a shame.

01:00:06.542 --> 01:00:08.127
If he hadn't canceled it,

01:00:08.669 --> 01:00:10.212
you could've held 700 million won
in your hands.

01:00:11.463 --> 01:00:13.215
You must have a lot of time on your hands

01:00:13.298 --> 01:00:15.300
to investigate a canceled policy.

01:00:16.468 --> 01:00:19.346
You couldn't receive the death benefit,
but the 200 million won premium

01:00:20.013 --> 01:00:21.765
was returned to Mr. Yoon's account.

01:00:22.516 --> 01:00:25.060
And you're assuming
that money came my way?

01:00:27.020 --> 01:00:30.441
You think I killed my fiancé
for a measly 200 million won?

01:00:34.361 --> 01:00:35.487
Tell me.

01:00:36.655 --> 01:00:40.701
What does his accident
have to do with what happened to Ms. Kim?

01:00:49.460 --> 01:00:50.586
I can smell it.

01:00:53.464 --> 01:00:54.715
The stench of someone…

01:00:56.758 --> 01:00:58.218
trading human lives for money.

01:01:40.928 --> 01:01:44.139
SPECIAL THANKS TO LEE ELIJAH
AND HA SEOKJIN FOR THEIR APPEARANCE

01:02:08.205 --> 01:02:11.124
What was Kim Yun-ji trying to reveal
before she was murdered?

01:02:12.376 --> 01:02:14.169
You've heard of Yoon Seung-jae, right?

01:02:14.795 --> 01:02:17.214
Kim Yun-ji and Yoon Seung-jae met,

01:02:18.257 --> 01:02:19.800
and they both died.

01:02:21.051 --> 01:02:22.261
Wrongful death?

01:02:22.970 --> 01:02:24.680
What about wrongful suspicion?

01:02:24.763 --> 01:02:25.931
A love triangle?

01:02:26.932 --> 01:02:28.767
The most common motive for murder
is love affairs.

01:02:29.685 --> 01:02:31.728
What is it that you really want to know?

01:02:31.812 --> 01:02:33.981
Your fiancé and Kim Yun-ji.

01:02:34.064 --> 01:02:35.065
Did you kill them?

01:02:39.653 --> 01:02:41.655
Subtitle: Jenny Kim